root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>768</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00CY</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00CY.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Breaking changes</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CW</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link
href="jms-00CW.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00CW">Forester 3.0</fr:link> introduces a number of breaking changes to the source language in order to facilitate maintainability, diagnostic support, and extensibility of both the <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> tool and your individual <fr:link
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000R">forests</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>764</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00CZ</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00CZ.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Fall-through of undefined identifiers</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CY</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The fall-through for undefined identifiers in XML mode is removed in <fr:link
href="jms-00CW.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00CW">Forester 3.0</fr:link>: previously when an identifier <fr:code>\foo</fr:code> was undefined, it was possible to write <fr:code>\foo[attr]{value}{body}</fr:code> and have this be rendered in XML to <fr:code>&lt;foo attr="value"&gt;body&lt;/foo&gt;</fr:code>.</fr:p><fr:p>This behavior has been removed, but you can nonetheless write <fr:code>\xml{foo}[attr]{value}{body}</fr:code> to achieve the same. For content that is being rendered by either LaTeX or KaTeX, simple fallthrough (naturally without attributes or arguments) is supported; therefore <fr:code> #{\alpha}</fr:code> will render to <fr:tex>\alpha</fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>766</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-00D0</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00D0.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Primitive formatting commands</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CY</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>As a consequence of the <fr:link
href="jms-00CZ.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00CZ">changed fallthrough behavior</fr:link>, several new primitives have been added to the source language, including <fr:code>\p</fr:code>, <fr:code>\em</fr:code>, <fr:code>\strong</fr:code>, <fr:code>\ol</fr:code>, <fr:code>\ul</fr:code>, <fr:code>\li</fr:code>, <fr:code>\blockquote</fr:code>, and <fr:code>\pre</fr:code>.</fr:p><fr:p>You can add further commands to your primitives using a combination of <fr:code>\def</fr:code>, <fr:code>\iftex</fr:code>, and <fr:code>\xml</fr:code>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="false"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="true"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>24322</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Release</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-009Q</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-009Q.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Forester 2.5</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>9</fr:month><fr:day>27</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link
href="dannypsnl.xml"
type="local"
addr="dannypsnl">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="vikramanchoudhury.xml"
type="local"
addr="vikramanchoudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</fr:link> for their suggestions and bug reports on the <fr:link
href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss"
type="external">mailing list</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:ul><fr:li>A new <fr:code>\iftex</fr:code> command has been added, following a suggestion of <fr:link
href="vikramanchoudhury.xml"
type="local"
addr="vikramanchoudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</fr:link>; this can be used to control the behavior of macros, depending on whether they are being rendered by <fr:tex>\LaTeX</fr:tex> or by the browser. For example, <fr:code>\iftex{foo}{bar}</fr:code> will become <fr:code>foo</fr:code> when passed to the <fr:tex>\LaTeX</fr:tex> tool, but will be reated as <fr:code>bar</fr:code> when rendering for the browser.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>A new <fr:link
href="jms-005O.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005O">fluid binding</fr:link> <fr:code>\transclude/taxon</fr:code> has been added to the <fr:link
href="jms-0067.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0067">transclusion overrides</fr:link>, which can be used to locally change the taxon of a transcluded tree. Thanks to <fr:link
href="dannypsnl.xml"
type="local"
addr="dannypsnl">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</fr:link> for implementing this.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>In order to support more modular development of <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000V">forests</fr:link>, a new <fr:code>theme</fr:code> directory is expected to contain all the XSL, CSS, font, etc. assets that pertain to the <fr:em>presentation</fr:em> of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000V">forest</fr:link>; the <fr:code>assets</fr:code> directory is meant to store things like images, PDFs, etc. that pertain to the <fr:em>content</fr:em> of your <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000V">forest</fr:link>. The simplest way to take advantage of this new feature is to bind your <fr:code>theme</fr:code> directory to a <fr:link
href="https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Tools-Submodules"
type="external">git submodule</fr:link> pointing to the <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme"
type="external">forester-base-theme</fr:link> repository. Your existing <fr:link
href="tfmt-000V.xml"
type="local"
addr="tfmt-000V">forest</fr:link> will still work fine for now even if you do not migrate to the new directory structure. I’m grateful to <fr:link
href="arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml"
type="local"
addr="armaëlguéneau">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link> for conversations that motivated me to make this change.</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
